	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I can't say for certain without reviewing the info, but I'm 99% sure that the lockout chip is the only difference.  They <em>might</em> require a RAM expansion in the NES, if they use RAM at $0800+ and above.  I don't know if they would even do that, depends on the game.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


