	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />AFAIK from random sources about the hotel Nintendo operations, the famicombox cartridges use a different lockout chip from all other regions, and suposedly like select PAL B cartridges, the PRG and CHR chips are wired to the lockout chip to disable when not authorized by the 'lock' chip.
<br />
<br />I'd love to see the front/back scans of the PCB of one of these games, since a quick look at the wiring could possibly prove this theory.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
